File: People queueing outside the offices of the South African Social Security Agency (Sassa). JOHANNESBURG - The South African Social Security Agency will make double payments of the R 350 special relief grants this week. According to a statement, the double payments are for outstanding June and July accounts. READ: How to apply for the COVID-19 special relief of distress grant Sassa has also reconsidered some applications for May and updated its database. "SASSA also reconsidered applications made in May against updated databases received, which resulted in an additional approximately 1 million applicants being approved for the grant," read the statement. Beneficiaries who receive their money through the Post Office have been advised to visit the premises only once they receive an SMS. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.